---
import '../styles/global.css';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import profilePic from '../assets/me.jpg';
import favicon from '../assets/favicon.svg';
import favicon96 from '../assets/favicon-96x96.png';
import faviconIco from '../assets/favicon.ico';
import appleIcon from '../assets/apple-touch-icon.png';
import siteManifest from '../assets/site.webmanifest';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>William L. Anderson</title>
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href={favicon96.src} sizes="96x96" />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href={favicon.src} />
    <link rel="shortcut icon" href={faviconIco.src} />
    <link rel="apple-touch-icon" sizes="180x180" href={appleIcon.src} />
    <link rel="manifest" href={siteManifest.src} />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Lora:ital,wght@0,400;0,500;0,600;1,400;1,500&family=Source+Serif+4:ital,opsz,wght@0,8..60,400;0,8..60,600;1,8..60,400&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <main class="container">
      <header class="hero">
        <div class="hero-top">
          <div class="profile-pic">
            <Image src={profilePic} alt="William L. Anderson" width={320} height={320} />
          </div>
          <div class="hero-title">
            <h1>William L. Anderson</h1>
            <div id="email-container" class="email">
              <noscript>hello [at] wlanderson [dot] com</noscript>
            </div>
            <nav class="topnav">
              <ul>
                <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
                <li><a href="/now">Now</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/william-l-anderson-a853b92aa/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://github.com/wlanderson0" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://wlandersons.substack.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Substack</a></li>
                <li><a href="/resume.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Resume</a></li>
              </ul>
            </nav>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="intro">
          Hi, I'm Will! I'm a <a href="https://www.matsprogram.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">MATS</a><sup class="note" tabindex="0">*<span class="note-content">The ML Alignment &amp; Theory Scholars program pairs fellows with alignment researchers for focused, full-time projects. Hover notes like this one are what I'd use for asides and sources.</span></sup> Fellow with the <a href="https://wittlab.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Oxford Witt Lab</a> and soon-to-be team lead at the <a href="https://www.cooperativeai.com/foundation" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Cooperative AI Foundation</a>. I work on multiagent security, national security, and generally making things go well. During my undergrad at UW–Madison, I was Director of the <a href="https://waisi.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Wisconsin AI Safety Initiative</a> and a Research Fellow at <a href="https://xrisk.uchicago.edu/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">UChicago XLab</a>. I have strong beliefs, weakly held, and update based on <a href="https://forms.gle/brAiMELagvQqUV1v9" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">feedback</a>.
        </p>
      </header>

      <hr class="rule ornament" />

      <section id="research">
        <h2>Research</h2>
        <p>My work focuses on the security risks that arise as increasingly capable AI agents proliferate and come into contact with one another. My technical work focuses on <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2505.02077" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">multi-agent security</a>, and my policy work focuses on the national security implications of AI.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>I'm a MATS Fellow in the Multiagent Security stream with <a href="https://wittlab.ai/author/christian-schroeder-de-witt/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Dr. Christian Schroeder de Witt</a>.</li>
          <li>I was a 2025 Summer Research Fellow at UChicago's Existential Risk Lab, where I worked on subtle attacks<sup class="note" tabindex="0">*<span class="note-content">Attacks where the adversarial signal is distributed across many interactions, so no single exchange looks malicious on its own.</span></sup> on multi-agent systems in critical infrastructure, advised by <a href="https://lewishammond.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Dr. Lewis Hammond</a>.</li>
          <li>I've got a series of pieces in the works on superintelligence deterrence (working with <a href="https://ari.us/team/morgan-c-plummer/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Morgan C. Plummer</a>). I also wrote about <a href="https://substack.com/home/post/p-183117624">managing US-ROK relations</a> amidst expanding export controls.</li>
          <li>I spent a year and change working on interpretability with Prof. <a href="https://pages.stat.wisc.edu/~zhong35/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Yiqiao Zhong</a> and Prof. <a href="https://junjiehu.github.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Junjie Hu</a>.</li>
          <li>In summer 2024, I completed the <a href="https://www.arena.education/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Alignment Research Engineer Accelerator</a> (ARENA) curriculum. I highly recommend others check it out, I've found no better way to quickly upskill in ML Safety.</li>
          <li>I advise <a href="https://secondlookresearch.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Second Look Research</a>, an organization focused on replicating AI safety research.</li>
          <li>I've given technical feedback and advice to many policy projects. I've also been told that I'm an excellent <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rubber_duck_debugging" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">rubber duck</a>. If either of these services would be helpful, feel free to reach out!</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <hr class="rule" />

      <section id="leadership">
        <h2>Leadership &amp; Involvement</h2>
        <p>During my undergrad, I was the Director of the <a href="https://waisi.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Wisconsin AI Safety Initiative</a>, a 501(c)(3) nonprofit of technical and policy researchers dedicated to guiding the development of advanced AI towards a future that benefits everyone.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>We had 120+ weekly active participants across our intro program and advanced reading groups. Our members have produced 20+ papers, published at ICML, ICLR, NeurIPS, and other top venues.</li>
          <li>We hosted an interdisciplinary panel on AI, featuring faculty from Education, Computer Sciences, and Philosophy. This spring, we're hosting the <a href="https://cdis.wisc.edu/ai-meets-society-aims-symposium/" rel="noopener noreferrer">AI Meets Society Symposium</a>, a 320-person conference bringing together AI researchers, policymakers, and industry leaders.</li>
          <li>I mentor AI Safety student organizers through <a href="https://kairos-project.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Kairos</a>'s Pathfinder program.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <hr class="rule" />

      <section id="talks">
        <h2>Talks</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><em>Organizer</em>, Research Process &amp; Technical AI Safety Workshops, AIMS Symposium, 2026</li>
          <li><em>Panelist</em>, Future of AI Panel, AIMS Symposium, 2026</li>
          <li><em>Multi-Agent Security Risks</em>, International Conference on Information Systems, 2025</li>
          <li><em>Panelist</em>, Wisconsin Technology Council Panel on AI Safety, 2025</li>
          <li><em>Diffuse Attacks on Multi-Agent AI Systems</em>, UChicago XLab Research Seminar, 2025</li>
          <li><em>A Case for Responsible AI</em>, IT Professionals Conference, 2025</li>
          <li><em>Sparse Models for Interpretability</em>, Yiqiao Zhong Summer Reading Group, 2025</li>
          <li><em>Security Risks in Multi-Agent AI Systems</em>, Advanced AI Congressional Exposition, 2025</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <hr class="rule" />

      <section id="awards">
        <h2>Awards &amp; Fellowships</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>2025 Summer Research Fellowship from UChicago XLab.</li>
          <li>2025–2026 Sophomore Research Fellowship from UW–Madison.</li>
          <li>2025 OpenPhil Action Fund University Organizer Fellowship.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <hr class="rule" />

      <section id="mentors">
        <h2>Mentorship</h2>
        <p>I've been lucky to have many incredible mentors throughout my life. A non-exhaustive list of thanks:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Professor Yiqiao Zhong, Dr. Lewis Hammond, Dr. Christian Schroeder de Witt, and Morgan Plummer, for all of their mentorship and kindness.</li>
          <li>Ben Hayum, Jeremy Kintana, and everyone else at WAISI for their wisdom, guidance, and friendship.</li>
          <li>John Bradley, Dan Bielski, Sean Kern, Zachary Ludvigson, and the many other wonderful coaches and teachers I've had.</li>
          <li>My parents and grandparents, who taught me a love of learning and the value of truth.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <hr class="rule" />

      <section id="personal">
        <h2>Personal</h2>
        <p>I'm a proud Minnesotan, and love the lakes, outdoors, cold, and snow. I was a competitive swimmer, captained my high school team, and worked during summers as a lifeguard. I've been vegetarian for about 6 years. Some other things I like:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Anki, Beli, Curius.</li>
          <li>Hats.</li>
          <li>Tolkien, Star Wars, GoT, Eragon, The Witcher, Monty Python, Tom Lehrer, <a href="/poetry">Shakespeare</a>, Henrik Karlsson (<a href="https://www.henrikkarlsson.xyz/p/looking-for-alice" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Looking for Alice</a>), <a href="https://www.astralcodexten.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Scott Alexander</a>, <a href="https://benkuhn.net/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Ben Kuhn</a>, and many others.</li>
          <li>History of (China, Egypt, English, Rome, Byzantium, England) Podcasts, Dwarkesh Patel, and the 80k Hours Podcast.</li>
          <li>Civilization V, Subnautica, Portal, Horizon: Zero Dawn/Forbidden West, etc.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <footer class="site-footer">
        <div class="site-chain">
          <a href="https://www.kaustubhais.com/">← Kaustubh</a>
          <a href="https://jeremykintana.com/">Jeremy →</a>
        </div>
        <p>© 2026 William L. Anderson</p>
      </footer>
    </main>

    <script>
      document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function () {
        const emailContainer = document.getElementById('email-container');
        if (!emailContainer) return;
        const user = 'hello';
        const domain = 'wlanderson';
        const tld = 'com';
        const link = document.createElement('a');
        link.href = 'mailto:' + user + '@' + domain + '.' + tld;
        link.textContent = user + ' [at] ' + domain + ' [dot] ' + tld;
        emailContainer.innerHTML = '';
        emailContainer.appendChild(link);
      });
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
